5000|$|The Defence Forces {{trace their}} origins to the Irish Volunteers, founded in 1913. Their {{official}} Irish-language title, Óglaigh na hÉireann, {{is taken from}} the equivalent Irish-language title of the Irish Volunteers, as are their cap badge and <b>the</b> <b>buttons</b> worn on ceremonial uniforms (<b>the</b> <b>buttons</b> are still marked with the initials [...] "IV".|$|R
